<p>
---Multiple Choice---

<p>
Choosing <tt>Multiple Choice</tt> as the question type loads the following screen as shown in Figure 3-11.

<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Multiple Choice Question">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/multiple-choice.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 3-11: Multiple Choice Question </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>
<tt>Question</tt>, <tt>Points</tt>, <tt>Subject</tt>, and <tt>Difficulty</tt> are discussed
in <a href="question-management.html">Section 2.3</a>.

<p> When the user clicks the <tt>Add Choice</tt> button, a new "Choice #" will appear, starting 
from 1 and incrementing by 1 each time. This section requires user input through the keyboard.

<p>
In a Multiple Choice Question, <tt>Answer</tt> is a heading with a series of boxes underneath. 
The user clicks the box to the right of every choice that is correct, a check appears in every box
that is marked.
<br> *note* If the user checks multiple boxes, then test takers will need to select all of these checked
boxes for their answer to be considered correct.

